# Time MCP Server Settings
# Use this file to configure the Time MCP server for Claude Desktop
#
# Format:
# SETTING_NAME=value
#
# Optional Settings:
# -----------------
# CONTAINER_NAME - Name of the Docker container (default: time-mcp-server)
# DOCKER_IMAGE - Docker image name and tag (default: mcp/time:latest)
# RESTART_CLAUDE - Whether to restart Claude Desktop if it's running (true/false, default: true)
# DEFAULT_TIMEZONE - Default timezone to use if not specified (default: system timezone)
#
# Examples:
# CONTAINER_NAME=my-time-server
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/time:custom
# RESTART_CLAUDE=false
# DEFAULT_TIMEZONE=America/New_York
#
# Default settings (uncomment and modify as needed):
# CONTAINER_NAME=time-mcp-server
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/time:latest
# RESTART_CLAUDE=true
# DEFAULT_TIMEZONE=
